cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use PurpleMCP-Lab in academic or applied research, please cite it."
title: "PurpleMCP-Lab: A Purple-Team Lab and Benchmark for Model Context Protocol Security"
abstract: >-
  PurpleMCP-Lab is a reproducible lab for building, attacking, and defending Model
  Context Protocol (MCP) servers. It pairs 27 attack modules and working exploits
  with hardened twins built on a reusable library of 22 guardrails, ships nine
  clean example servers (several wired to live APIs — weather, crypto, web search,
  threat-intel, and DNS), maps every module to OWASP LLM Top 10 / CWE / MITRE ATLAS, and
  includes PurpleMCP-Bench — a deterministic guardrail-effectiveness benchmark plus
  an optional LLM-susceptibility evaluation — with machine-readable (JSON/SARIF)
  output and a light "Sorbet" desktop GUI.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Parshad
    given-names: Kailash
repository-code: "https://github.com/Krishita17/purplemcp-lab"
